  "metamarket_info_item_technique_abyssor_details": "✦ ABYSSOR. underwater apparatus for pressure zones and hidden routes.\n\n◆ Visual signature: sealed pressure hulls, quiet lights and a feeling of controlled depth. ABYSSOR is read first through its silhouette: proportions, light, mass and motion make the asset recognizable before any stat is shown.\n\n◇ Origin layer: It seems born near abyssal docks where light is rare and pressure decides design. This source layer connects the machine to a specific world, industry, route or civilization, making the asset feel earned.\n\n✧ Functional vector: It may become a survey platform, opening maps, resource traces and safe routes for future expeditions. This role lets the object speak through movement: cargo, scouting, protection, extraction, command or prestige.\n\n⬡ Future role: Its supply and price place it closer to accessible infrastructure, yet the object still keeps a personal serial trace. Inside Quantum Universe it may become a machine that marks where the owner can go, what they can build and how they appear.\n\n◈ Owner resonance: For a collector, ABYSSOR becomes a compact legend of engineering, scarcity and future utility. 🌊",
  "metamarket_info_item_technique_aerolyth_description": "AEROLYTH: spacecraft built for deep routes, orbital maneuvers and distant sectors.",
  "metamarket_info_item_technique_aerolyth_details": "✦ AEROLYTH. This asset reads as spacecraft built for deep routes, orbital maneuvers and distant sectors.\n\n◆ Visual signature: crystal geometry, hard reflections and a precise technological glow. Its card should feel like a separate machine passport, where contour, color and engineering mood explain why AEROLYTH belongs here.\n\n◇ Origin layer: Its blueprint belongs to orbital yards where every contour is tested against vacuum and acceleration. The provenance adds weight to the serial trace: AEROLYTH enters MetaMarket as a vehicle with memory, not a nameless render.\n\n✧ Functional vector: It may serve as a jump asset, connecting distant points, rare missions and travel layers inside QL7 GameVerse. The functional direction respects supply, price pressure and visual weight, so economy and fantasy move together.\n\n⬡ Future role: Its rarity feels strategic, closer to a faction instrument than a simple collectible vehicle. The vehicle may one day serve as a bridge between collection, gameplay, reputation and digital territory.\n\n◈ Owner resonance: Its owner receives not only a vehicle image, but a serial trace that can grow with the metaverse. 🚀",
  "metamarket_info_item_technique_aeroryn_description": "AERORYN: air machine that carries the memory of sky, risk and navigation.",
